

Even if I try to calculate the muscle cell length in the x direction it will count based in pixels 

So even if the muscle gets squeezed at the bottom part such that it is getting more triangular, the upper part of the 
muscle is still the same length as before. in the upper part the muscle x length is still conserved.

## So the area is not changing i.e not increasing or decreasing. The area is conserved. 

## Now since in reality its a 3d object, the squeezing will result in elongation in the z-direction. So not necessarily it will elongate 
or deform in the y direction if squeezed from x-direction 

##
 if a cell is changing shape from one msc to the other in cc3d then possibly what might be happening. Because area is conserved.  

 
==================================================================================================================================== 
Inertia tensor in CompuCell3D is a mathematical way of describing how the shape and mass of a cell are spread around its center. It doesnâ€™t 
tell you where the cell is. It tells you how its shape is distributed relative to the center

the cell changes shape, the position of the center of mass moves.

If center of mass changes the moment of inertia also changes. 

